    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5307: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shoemaker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-11T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 11, 1931—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 11—8:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. With reference to my telegram 29, November 6, 5 p.m. Bulgarian Minister at
                    Athens has telegraphed that the Greek Government has amended its reply as
                    follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Withdrawal of K[afandaris]–M[olloff] dispute from the Hague Court no
                            longer insisted upon;</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Bulgarian reserve to the effect that the proposed agreement shall be
                            without prejudice to rights under K–M convention, to be withdrawn from
                            body of agreement and incorporated in Unilauf [<hi rend="italic"
                                >unilateral?</hi>] declaration;</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Greece to declare that should Bulgaria cease at any time to pay
                            reparations without the express consent of Greece, the latter will
                            refuse to honor bonds deposited by it under article 5 of K–M
                            convention.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The Secretary General of the Foreign Office believes that amended reply offers
                    possibility of agreement in the event Bulgaria can be certain that Greece will
                    fulfill its obligation to deposit the K–M bonds for the 30-year period on
                    December 15th of this year. Stoyanoff is returning from Athens to supply full
                    particulars to Cabinet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shoemaker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
